An insight into how perceptions of the Amazon rainforest 
as an unspoilt natural wilderness could be changed by 
recent evidence suggesting traces of man-made 
structures can be discerned within its confines. The 
programme also assesses what these discoveries mean 
for the Amazon's status as a rallying cause for the 
international environmental movement. Narrated by 
Deborah MacLaren.
